4 SJR___ NAMING PORTIONS OF ALABAMA STATE ROUTES 5, 69, 195,
5 AND 257, AS WELL AS INDUSTRIAL PARKWAY, IN WALKER COUNTY,
6 ALABAMA, AS THE SMITH LAKE PARKWAY.
7
8 WHEREAS, it is with due consideration for the role
9 that Smith Lake plays in the tourism-related economy of
10 Walker County and North Alabama that this body requests that
11 the Department of Transportation designate a route to be
12 named Smith Lake Parkway beginning at Exit 65 on Interstate
13 22, Industrial Parkway, to the intersection with SR5/SR69
14 West to the intersection with SR195 North to the
15 intersection with SR257 North, ending at the county line
16 between Walker and Winston Counties where the Arley - Smith
17 Lake Parkway begins; and
18 WHEREAS, Smith Lake is a popular destination in the
19 region and providing signage for the Smith Lake Parkway to
20 interstate drivers is an opportunity to showcase the
21 destination to potential visitors; prominent signage at
22 intersections throughout the route will guide visitors along
23 the parkway to their recreation destination; and
24 WHEREAS, tourism plays a significant role in the
25 economy of Walker County with attractions such as Smith Lake
26 drawing visitors for boating, fishing, and other outdoor
27 recreational activities; the natural beauty and recreational
28 opportunities offered by Smith Lake contribute to the area's
Page 1

opportunities offered by Smith Lake contribute to the area's
SJR17 INTRODUCED
29 appeal to tourists and residents alike, bolstering the local
30 economy through tourism-related businesses and services
31 offered along the parkway; now therefore,
32 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
33 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That for due consideration for
34 the role that Smith Lake plays in the tourism-related
35 economy of Walker County, the Department of Transportation
36 is encouraged to coordinate with local governing officials
37 to consider naming the Smith Lake Parkway, a route that will
38 run from Interstate 22 to the border of Walker and Winston
39 Counties, and to erect several appropriate signs or markers
40 along the route, with consideration to fiscal
41 responsibility, consistent with applicable requirements and
42 laws, in recognition of this designation.
